SUMMARY:Winter Evenings with Edgar Allan Poe Inspired Stories at the Olde Mill Restaurant
DESCRIPTION:Spirits\, Shadows & Storytelling: Winter Evenings with Edgar Allan Poe at the Olde Mill Restaurant\nThis winter\, the Olde Mill Restaurant in Intercourse\, PA invites guests to step into a world of shadows\, suspense\, and Poe-inspired intrigue. Spirits\, Shadows & Storytelling is a series of chilling evenings blending dramatic tales\, handcrafted cocktails\, and period dining. \nAcclaimed storyteller Bill Wood will lead audiences through performances inspired by Edgar Allan Poe as well as eerie local legends passed down through generations. Each evening is designed to immerse guests in the haunting atmosphere of mystery and suspense. \nAdding to the experience\, Waltz Vineyards will serve Victorian-era cocktails while the Olde Mill kitchen prepares period-inspired menu specials. Together\, they create a setting where history\, storytelling\, and community come alive. \nOwner Carl Kosko of the Inn & Spa at Intercourse Village notes that some evenings may even pair with their signature murder mystery parties\, offering guests a full weekend of suspense and surprise. \nThere is no entrance fee—guests may enjoy stories\, food\, and drinks at their leisure. Story Time begins at 6:30 p.m. \nEvent Dates: Nov. 22\, Dec. 20\, Jan. 23\, Feb. 27\, Mar. 27Location: Olde Mill Restaurant\, 9 Queen Street\, Intercourse\, PA \nSeating is first-come\, first-served; early arrival is encouraged.
URL:https://lancasterpa.com/events-calendar/winter-evenings-with-edgar-allan-poe-inspired-stories-at-the-olde-mill-restaurant/2026-03-27/
LOCATION:Inn & Spa at Intercourse Village\, 3542 Old Philadelphia Pike (Rt. 340)\, Intercourse\, PA\, 17534\, United States
CATEGORIES:Murder Mystery
