SUMMARY:Robert Fulton Volunteer Fire Company Mud Sale
DESCRIPTION:If you’re looking for something to do this weekend\, might we suggest a trip to Peach Bottom\, PA for the annual Robert Fulton Spring Auction. \nStarting at 8:00 am\, the mud sale kicks off with a full day of auctions.  Sale items range from livestock to quilts and many item in between. \nThe Robert Fulton Volunteer Fire Company Mud Sale usually falls on the 1st Saturday of April every year. \n\nMud Sales are a unique Lancaster County tradition to raise funds for local volunteer fire companies. See our complete schedule of Lancaster County Mud Sales. \nPlease Note: Many of the Fire Companies holding mud sales can always use extra help on the days they receive items and the day of the event.  It takes a LOT of labor to put on a mud sale.
URL:https://lancasterpa.com/events-calendar/robert-fulton-volunteer-fire-company-mud-sale/2026-04-04/
